  "text": "Apache Kafka's log compaction architecture consists of several key components working together to implement key-based deduplication in log segments. The main cleaner thread is implemented in LogCleaner.java (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/LogCleaner.java), which extends ShutdownableThread and orchestrates the overall cleaning process by selecting logs to clean and delegating to the Cleaner class. The core cleaning logic resides in Cleaner.java (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/Cleaner.java), which implements the actual key-based deduplication mechanism. Cleaner.java contains critical methods: buildOffsetMap() and buildOffsetMapForSegment() construct a key=>offset mapping for the dirty section of the log, while shouldRetainRecord() implements the deduplication logic that retains only the latest record for each key. The deduplication uses a hash-based offset map interface defined in OffsetMap.java, with SkimpyOffsetMap.java providing the implementation that uses cryptographic hashing (MD5 by default) to store key hashes with their associated offsets, using linear probing for collision resolution. Segment selection is managed by LogCleanerManager.java (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/LogCleanerManager.java), which calculates which logs need cleaning based on a dirtiness ratio (the ratio of uncleanable bytes to total bytes). LogToClean.java (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/LogToClean.java) represents a log ready for cleaning and calculates the cleanableRatio metric that prioritizes which logs are dirtiest. The cleaner groups segments by size using groupSegmentsBySize() in Cleaner.java to prevent excessive segment fragmentation. For transactional support, CleanedTransactionMetadata.java manages aborted transaction state during cleaning, AbortedTxn.java represents aborted transactions, and TransactionIndex.java maintains indexes of aborted transactions. Configuration is centralized in CleanerConfig.java with parameters like deduplication buffer size, IO buffer size, and thread count. LogCleaningState.java defines the state machine for cleaning progress (InProgress, Aborted, Paused). Statistics are collected in CleanerStats.java and PreCleanStats.java to monitor cleaning performance and progress."
}

